  "texts": [
    "In addition to this, challenges like patient data privacy, model interpretability, and potential algorithmic bias are crucial in clinical AI, especially in oncology.",
    "These issues drive research focus and impact public trust and acceptance of AI in healthcare.",
    "A thorough examination of these obstacles could offer valuable insights into what is needed to ensure the safe and fair integration of AI in breast cancer diagnosis and treatment.",
    "[40] Future research directions may involve the combination of AI with genomics and molecular data to enhance precision medicine, as well as the development of models that can better interpret imaging data with minimal human supervision.",
    "However, current barriers include the lack of large, annotated datasets, regulatory hurdles, and concerns over AI's interpretability and ethical use, especially regarding patient privacy and data security."
